10 An Act relating to credit sales; amending 14A O.S.
2021, Sections 2-211 and 2-417, which relate to
11 discounts and surcharges for certain transactions;
requiring certain actions from sellers when imposing
12 a surcharge on certain transactions; modifying
definitions; updating statutory language; and
13 providing an effective date.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 14A O.S. 2021, Section 2-211, is
18 amended to read as follows:
19 Section 2-211. A. With respect to all sales transactions, a
20 discount which a seller offers, allows, or otherwise makes available
21 for the purpose of inducing payment by cash, check, or similar means
22 rather than by use of an open-end credit card account or debit card
23 account shall not constitute a credit service charge as determined
24 under Section 2-109 of this title if the discount is offered to all
Req. No. 1701 Page 1
1 pros pective buyers clearly and conspicuously in accordance with
2 regulations of the Administrator of Consumer Affairs Credit. No
3 There shall not be a limit on the discount that may be offered by
4 the seller. Pursuant to the regulations of the Administrator, a
5 seller who provides a discount not in accordance with regulations
6 shall disclose such information to the Administrator.
7 B. A seller in any sales transaction may pass on the processing
8 fee or impose a surcharge on a cardholder who elects to pay using an
9 open-end credit card or debit card account instead of paying by
10 cash, check, or similar means. There is no limit on the discount
11 which may be offered by the seller. A seller who provides a
12 discount otherwise than in accordance with the regulations of the
13 Administrator must make the disclosures required by those
14 regulations If a seller elects to pass on the credit card or debit
15 card processing fee, or impose a surcharge for the use of an open-
16 end credit card or debit card account, the charged amount shall:
17 1. Be listed as separate line items in the cardholder’s
18 receipt; and
19 2. Not exceed the total of the bank processing fees, financial
20 transaction fees, the cost of providing for secure transaction,
21 portal fees, and fees necessary to compensate for increased
22 bandwidth incurred as a result of providing the transaction.
23 B. C. A seller who is registered with the United States
24 Treasury Department of the Treasury as a money transmitter pursuant
Req. No. 1701 Page 2
1 to 3 1 CFR C.F.R., Section 103.41, and who provides an electronic
2 funds transmission service, including service by telephone and the
3 Internet, may charge a different price for a funds transmission
4 service based on the mode of transmission used in the transaction
5 without violating this section so long as the price charged for a
6 service paid for with an open-end credit card or debit card account
7 is not greater than the price charged for such service if paid for
8 with currency or other similar means accepted within the same mode
9 of transmission.
10 C. D. Any seller subject to the provisions of subsection B C of
11 this section shall either conduct business at a location in this
12 state or comply with the provisions of Section 1022 of Title 18 of
13 the Oklahoma Statutes.
14 D. E. As used in this section, “debit:
15 1. “Debit card” means any instrument or device, whether known
16 as a debit card or by any other name, issued with or without fee by
17 an issuer for the use of the cardholder in depositing, obtaining, or
18 transferring funds from a consumer banking electronic facility; and
19 2. “Surcharge” means any means of increasing the regular or
20 advertised price to a cardholder, which is not imposed upon
21 customers paying by cash, check, or similar means.
22 E. For purposes of this section, a private educational
23 institution as defined in paragraph (e) of Section 3102 of Title 70
24 of the Oklahoma Statutes, a private school defined as a nonpublic
Req. No. 1701 Page 3
1 enti ty conducting an educational program for at least one grade
2 between prekindergarten through twelve, a municipality as defined in
3 paragraph 5 of Section 1-102 of Title 11 of the Oklahoma Statutes or
4 a public trust with a municipality as its beneficiary may charge a
5 service fee. The service fee shall be limited to bank processing
6 fees and financial transaction fees, the cost of providing for
7 secure transaction, portal fees, and fees necessary to compensate
8 for increased bandwidth incurred as a result of providing for an
9 online transaction.
10 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 14A O.S. 2021, Section 2-417, is
11 amended to read as follows:
12 Section 2-417. A. No seller in any sales transaction may
13 impose a surcharge on a cardholder who elects to use a credit card
14 or debit card in lieu of payment by cash, check or similar means A
15 seller in any sales transaction may pass on the processing fee or
16 impose a surcharge on a cardholder who elects to pay using an open-
17 end credit card or debit card account instead of paying by cash,
18 check, or similar means. If a seller elects to pass on the credit
19 card or debit card processing fee, or impose a surcharge for the use
20 of an open-end credit card or debit card account, the charged amount
21 shall:
22 1. Be listed as a separate line item on the cardholder’s
23 receipt; and
24
