1 2. Not exceed the total of the bank processing fees, financial
2 transaction fees, the cost of providing for secure transaction,
3 portal fees, and fees necessary to compensate for increased
4 bandwidth incurred as a result of providing the transaction.
5 B. As used in this section, “debit:
6 1. “Debit card” means any instrument or device, whether known
7 as a debit card or by any other name, issued with or without fee by
8 an issuer for the use of the cardholder in depositing, obtaining, or
9 transferring funds from a consumer banking electronic facility; and
10 2. “Surcharge” means any means of increasing the regular or
11 advertised price to a cardholder, which is not imposed upon
