13 C. For purposes of this section, a private educational
14 institution as defined in paragraph (e) of Section 3102 of Title 70
15 of the Oklahoma Statutes, a private school defined as a nonpublic
16 entity conducting an educational program for at least one grade
17 between prekindergarten through twelve, a municipality as defined in
18 paragraph 5 of Section 1-102 of Title 11 of the Oklahoma Statutes or
19 a public trust with a municipality as its beneficiary may charge a
20 service fee. The service fee may be applied to online or in-person
21 transactions and shall be used to offset bank processing fees,
22 financial transaction fees, the cost of providing for secure
23 transaction, portal fees, and fees necessary to compensate for
